<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="39" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1096,1548]" pageId="10" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1096,1122]" pageId="10" pageNumber="39">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Head extremely small compared to thorax. Eyes pilose, widely separated above and below antenna, except in 
<taxonomicName box="[376,510,1136,1161]" class="Insecta" family="Acroceridae" genus="Pialea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capitella">
<emphasis box="[376,510,1136,1161]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="39">P. capitella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Ocellar tubercle raised (
<figureCitation box="[813,949,1136,1162]" captionStart="FIGURES 24, 25. 24" captionStartId="7.[151,269,840,864]" captionTargetBox="[186,1419,194,810]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[176,1420,194,812]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 24, 25. 24. Head, dorsal view, Pialea sp. 1; 25. Head, dorsal view, Pialea sp. 2." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189344/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="39">
Fig. 
<number box="[869,949,1136,1162]" pageId="10" pageNumber="39" value="24.25">24, 25</number>
</figureCitation>
). Scapes totally (
<figureCitation box="[1154,1241,1136,1162]" captionStart="FIGURES 24, 25. 24" captionStartId="7.[151,269,840,864]" captionTargetBox="[186,1419,194,810]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[176,1420,194,812]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 24, 25. 24. Head, dorsal view, Pialea sp. 1; 25. Head, dorsal view, Pialea sp. 2." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189344/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="39">
Fig. 
<number box="[1210,1241,1136,1162]" pageId="10" pageNumber="39" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
) or only basally fused (
<figureCitation box="[236,331,1174,1200]" captionStart="FIGURES 24, 25. 24" captionStartId="7.[151,269,840,864]" captionTargetBox="[186,1419,194,810]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[176,1420,194,812]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 24, 25. 24. Head, dorsal view, Pialea sp. 1; 25. Head, dorsal view, Pialea sp. 2." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189344/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="39">
Fig. 
<number box="[296,331,1174,1200]" pageId="10" pageNumber="39" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
); pedicel shorter than the scapes (
<figureCitation box="[759,902,1174,1200]" captionStart="FIGURES 24, 25. 24" captionStartId="7.[151,269,840,864]" captionTargetBox="[186,1419,194,810]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[176,1420,194,812]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 24, 25. 24. Head, dorsal view, Pialea sp. 1; 25. Head, dorsal view, Pialea sp. 2." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189344/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="39">
Fig. 
<number box="[819,902,1174,1200]" pageId="10" pageNumber="39" value="24.25">24, 25</number>
</figureCitation>
); flagellum longer than the head. Humeral crossvein absent; wing venation variable (
<figureCitation box="[644,732,1213,1239]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="7.[151,255,1346,1370]" captionTargetBox="[179,1393,915,1305]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[179,1423,899,1340]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 26. Wing, dorsal view, Pialea sp. 1." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189345/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="39">
Fig. 
<number box="[699,732,1213,1239]" pageId="10" pageNumber="39" value="26.0">26</number>
</figureCitation>
). Sexual dimorphism conspicuous in length and insertion of antennae and in wing length. Scapes attached to ventral surface of antennal tubercle in the female and to its anterior surface in the male. Also, antenna inserts at mid-eye or below in the female and well above the mideye in the male. Wing extends past abdomen in the female, while in male is approximately even with abdomen tip.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
